classes.label: AuthenticationExpiredError
description:
While performing some reporting action, like fetching data from ES, our
access token expired.

classes.label: DisallowedOutgoingUrl
description: While loading requests in the Kibana app, a URL was encountered that the network policy did not allow.

classes.label: InvalidLayoutParametersError
description: While validating the page layout parameters for a screenshot type report job

children.label: code
description:
A string that uniquely brands an error type. This is used to power telemetry
about reporting failures.

classes.label: UnknownError
description: An unknown error has occurred. See details.

classes.label: VisualReportingSoftDisabledError
description:
Special error case that should only occur on Cloud when trying to generate
a report on a Kibana instance that is too small to be running Chromium.

children.label: humanFriendlyMessage
description: Return a message describing the error that is human friendly

children.label: GENERATE_PREFIX
description:
/**
   * Public endpoint for POST URL strings and automated report generation
   * exportTypeId is added to the final path
   */

children.label: DOWNLOAD_PREFIX
description:
/**
     * Public endpoint used by Watcher and automated report downloads
     * jobId is added to the final path
     */

children.label: DELETE_PREFIX
description:
/**
     * Public endpoint potentially used to delete a report after download in automation
     * jobId is added to the final path
     */
